Software Requirements Specification (SRS)
GlobalMart - Cross-border E-commerce Experience Platform
Version 1.0

1. Introduction

1.1 Purpose
This document defines the requirements for GlobalMart, a cross-border e-commerce platform designed for international students in China.

1.2 Scope
GlobalMart will allow users to browse products, view prices in multiple currencies, manage shopping cart, simulate payments, and track orders.

1.3 Target Users
- International students in China
- Age: 18-35
- Tech-savvy, smartphone users
- Need bilingual support

2. Overall Description

2.1 Product Perspective
GlobalMart is a web-based application with frontend (HTML/CSS/JS), backend (Python/Flask), and SQLite database.

2.2 User Characteristics
- Technical Level: Moderate
- Language: English or Chinese
- Access: Desktop and mobile browsers

3. Functional Requirements

FR1: User Registration (Must)
FR2: User Login (Must)
FR3: Browse Products (Must)
FR4: Product Search (Should)
FR5: Multi-currency Display (Should)
FR6: Shopping Cart (Must)
FR7: Wishlist (Could)
FR8: Price Comparison (Could)
FR9: Checkout (Must)
FR10: Payment Simulation (Must)
FR11: Order History (Should)
FR12: Logistics Tracking (Could)
FR13: User Reviews (Should)
FR15: Language Toggle (Could)

4. Non-Functional Requirements

NFR1: Performance - Page load under 3 seconds
NFR2: Usability - Intuitive UI with clear navigation
NFR3: Security - Password encryption, HTTPS
NFR4: Reliability - 99% uptime
NFR5: Scalability - 100 concurrent users for demo
NFR6: Compatibility - Chrome, Firefox, Safari

5. Constraints
- Web-only (no mobile app)
- Payment simulation only (no real payment)
- 12-week development timeline
- Team size: 2 developers

6. Assumptions
- Users have basic internet access
- Users can read English or Chinese
- Demo will be shown on desktop/laptop

